- "blossomed with more than one visit" refers to packages that have been accessed more than once in the last six months;
- "seed of vulnerability" refers to packages that have associated vulnerabilities;
- "digital garden of software" is a metaphor for the software repository.

sql:
SELECT AVG(overall_score) AS average_overall_score
FROM packages
WHERE last_updated >= DATE('now', '-6 months');

